1
00:01:06,336 --> 00:01:10,778
=The Truth=

2
00:01:11,480 --> 00:01:14,136
=Episode 13=

3
00:01:14,712 --> 00:01:16,951
Big data is really helpful.

4
00:01:17,272 --> 00:01:21,231
It saves me from having to stay up late
watching surveillance footage.

5
00:01:21,231 --> 00:01:22,472
It's more efficient.

6
00:01:23,591 --> 00:01:25,552
Unexpectedly,
after searching high and low,

7
00:01:26,311 --> 00:01:28,712
it was right under our noses all along.

8
00:01:31,712 --> 00:01:34,272
The traffic police said
this car was towed here a week ago.

9
00:01:35,272 --> 00:01:39,192
It was found stuck in a drainage ditch
leading from Sishui River to the city.

10
00:01:39,791 --> 00:01:41,112
The road conditions are poor.

11
00:01:41,552 --> 00:01:43,871
Perhaps in the dark,
the driver didn't see it and drove in.

12
00:01:44,992 --> 00:01:46,712
The fuel tank's practically empty.

13
00:01:54,352 --> 00:01:56,552
There are cosmetic smudges
and some long hair

14
00:01:57,431 --> 00:01:58,752
on the bottom of the trunk.

15
00:01:58,992 --> 00:02:01,031
I'll take them back for testing

16
00:02:01,031 --> 00:02:02,791
to confirm if they belong to the victim.

17
00:02:28,991 --> 00:02:30,872
The car accidentally ended up
in the ditch.

18
00:02:31,072 --> 00:02:32,951
It definitely wasn't part
of the killer's plan.

19
00:02:33,111 --> 00:02:35,752
So in panic, he wouldn't have had time
to properly clean the car.

20
00:02:35,752 --> 00:02:36,551
Search carefully.

21
00:02:36,551 --> 00:02:37,951
We might find something crucial.

22
00:02:49,208 --> 00:02:50,013
(Insulin Injection)

23
00:02:53,912 --> 00:02:54,752
Little Qian.

24
00:02:56,192 --> 00:02:56,711
Yes?

25
00:02:57,391 --> 00:02:58,711
You're just standing there...

26
00:03:01,951 --> 00:03:04,111
Magnetic car camera.

27
00:03:04,511 --> 00:03:06,671
It must've fallen off
when the car jolted.

28
00:04:23,591 --> 00:04:27,192
Does the evidence we collected
directly link to this vehicle?

29
00:04:29,151 --> 00:04:29,951
Already tested.

30
00:04:30,192 --> 00:04:31,552
The wear patterns on the tires

31
00:04:31,552 --> 00:04:34,471
match the tire marks
at the riverside dump site exactly.

32
00:04:34,951 --> 00:04:37,911
Also, the dent on the rear of the car

33
00:04:38,031 --> 00:04:40,552
is basically identical
to the one seen in the video.

34
00:04:40,591 --> 00:04:42,591
On the trunk lining,

35
00:04:42,591 --> 00:04:46,232
I found cosmetic residue matching
the ingredients of the victim's makeup.

36
00:04:46,471 --> 00:04:48,591
And the hair was confirmed
to be the victim's.

37
00:04:49,112 --> 00:04:51,232
We also found the insulin
left behind in the car.

38
00:04:51,232 --> 00:04:53,351
The suspect we just saw in the video

39
00:04:53,591 --> 00:04:54,632
is very thin.

40
00:04:54,632 --> 00:04:56,232
And he was sweating.

41
00:04:56,232 --> 00:04:58,711
So there was a lot of sweat residue
on the steering wheel.

42
00:04:58,872 --> 00:04:59,872
The DNA extracted from it

43
00:04:59,872 --> 00:05:01,351
matches what we found earlier.

44
00:05:03,232 --> 00:05:07,072
The car registration information shows
this car is registered under Huitongda.

45
00:05:07,232 --> 00:05:08,351
Wang Meng confessed

46
00:05:08,511 --> 00:05:09,911
that he had his secretary

47
00:05:09,911 --> 00:05:11,711
arrange this car for Zhan Qiuman's use.

48
00:05:14,031 --> 00:05:16,992
This person clearly didn't know
there was a dashcam in the car.

49
00:05:16,992 --> 00:05:19,271
He's most likely not from Huitongda.

50
00:05:19,271 --> 00:05:21,312
Then who could he be?

51
00:05:21,752 --> 00:05:23,471
Judging from the first video clip,

52
00:05:23,471 --> 00:05:25,632
the place where the suspect
put the victim into the car

53
00:05:26,112 --> 00:05:27,831
is probably not far
from the primary scene.

54
00:05:28,072 --> 00:05:30,232
It looks like a parking lot
of a residential complex.

55
00:05:30,552 --> 00:05:33,232
It's just too dark
to make out any details.

56
00:05:34,432 --> 00:05:36,031
I can improve it.

57
00:05:37,632 --> 00:05:39,831
But look at this image.

58
00:05:44,232 --> 00:05:44,911
Well...

59
00:05:45,391 --> 00:05:46,992
Something "He" and something "Yuan"?

60
00:05:49,591 --> 00:05:51,271
Search citywide
for residential complexes

61
00:05:51,511 --> 00:05:53,471
with names
containing both "He" and "Yuan".

62
00:05:54,031 --> 00:05:56,711
The property management
should give us key leads.

63
00:06:06,591 --> 00:06:08,752
The property management
of Hexie Jiayuan has confirmed

64
00:06:08,752 --> 00:06:10,232
that the man is a tenant.

65
00:06:10,831 --> 00:06:12,632
But he's not the actual tenant.

66
00:06:13,192 --> 00:06:15,432
They have contacted the landlord
and the leaseholder.

67
00:06:15,752 --> 00:06:16,920
The landlord is out of town.

68
00:06:17,112 --> 00:06:18,792
The leaseholder should be here shortly.

69
00:06:23,432 --> 00:06:24,391
Pang Xianglan?

70
00:06:25,432 --> 00:06:27,232
You rented apartment 1008?

71
00:06:29,192 --> 00:06:31,031
I-I rented it for my brother.

72
00:06:32,632 --> 00:06:34,112
Why did you suddenly call me here?

73
00:06:35,511 --> 00:06:37,112
Has something happened?

74
00:06:40,031 --> 00:06:41,232
Is this man your brother?

75
00:06:43,992 --> 00:06:45,072
Yes.

76
00:07:31,031 --> 00:07:31,911
He's dead.

77
00:07:34,432 --> 00:07:35,632
Notify the forensic unit.

78
00:07:36,031 --> 00:07:36,911
Yes, Captain Leng.

79
00:07:58,792 --> 00:08:01,232
The time of death
is at least three days ago.

80
00:08:02,112 --> 00:08:06,591
The low temperature from the AC
slowed down the decomposition.

81
00:08:07,192 --> 00:08:08,112
It could be earlier.

82
00:08:09,552 --> 00:08:13,232
He probably died
not long after dumping the body.

83
00:08:16,511 --> 00:08:17,711
The door lock was intact.

84
00:08:18,112 --> 00:08:19,391
He was alone in the apartment.

85
00:08:20,031 --> 00:08:21,872
Even though he knew he had diabetes,

86
00:08:22,271 --> 00:08:23,992
he still ate sweets and drank beer.

87
00:08:24,831 --> 00:08:26,872
Master, what do you think?

88
00:08:30,911 --> 00:08:32,072
What's that woman's name?

89
00:08:34,951 --> 00:08:35,751
Pang Xianglan.

90
00:08:36,111 --> 00:08:36,991
And her brother?

91
00:08:39,072 --> 00:08:40,111
Pang Xinghua.

92
00:08:48,072 --> 00:08:51,231
Pang Xinghua's DNA matches the DNA found
under Zhan Qiuman's fingernails.

93
00:08:51,392 --> 00:08:53,312
(DNA Report)
Defensive wounds were found on his body.

94
00:08:53,912 --> 00:08:55,272
The estimated time of death is

95
00:08:55,272 --> 00:08:56,951
the day after Zhan Qiuman was killed.

96
00:08:57,631 --> 00:09:00,552
Signs of a struggle were found
at Pang Xinghua's apartment.

97
00:09:00,831 --> 00:09:05,591
The shape of Zhan Qiuman's head wound
matches the edge of the end table.

98
00:09:05,951 --> 00:09:08,751
We can infer that Pang Xinghua's home
was the primary crime scene.

99
00:09:09,991 --> 00:09:14,552
His computer showed frequent logins
to overseas gambling websites.

100
00:09:14,871 --> 00:09:18,831
His phone also had calls and messages
from online loan companies

101
00:09:18,831 --> 00:09:20,111
demanding repayment.

102
00:09:20,711 --> 00:09:23,072
The due date
for his debts was a week ago.

103
00:09:24,111 --> 00:09:25,111
That means

104
00:09:25,751 --> 00:09:28,512
Pang Xinghua killed Zhan Qiuman
for money.

105
00:09:29,991 --> 00:09:34,751
The cause of Pang Xinghua's death
was ketoacidosis.

106
00:09:35,871 --> 00:09:37,231
It's a complication of diabetes.

107
00:09:37,792 --> 00:09:39,111
If rescue is timely,

108
00:09:39,111 --> 00:09:40,231
it might not lead to death.

109
00:09:40,991 --> 00:09:42,991
What was found
in the car was regular insulin.

110
00:09:43,512 --> 00:09:45,471
This means
Pang Xinghua needs multiple injections

111
00:09:45,471 --> 00:09:47,871
within a day to control his condition.

112
00:09:48,552 --> 00:09:50,591
However, based on the dash cam video,

113
00:09:51,272 --> 00:09:53,871
from loading the body
into the car to dumping it,

114
00:09:53,871 --> 00:09:55,111
and finally abandoning the car,

115
00:09:55,392 --> 00:09:57,552
it took about six hours in total.

116
00:09:57,751 --> 00:09:59,552
Lasting this long
without injecting medication

117
00:09:59,552 --> 00:10:01,192
is extremely dangerous for him.

118
00:10:01,351 --> 00:10:03,912
The elevator surveillance
didn't capture him moving the body.

119
00:10:03,912 --> 00:10:06,631
That means Pang Xinghua used the stairs
to move the body.

120
00:10:06,792 --> 00:10:08,032
Although the floor wasn't high,

121
00:10:08,032 --> 00:10:10,751
intense physical activity combined
with strong emotional stress

122
00:10:10,751 --> 00:10:12,152
would affect his endocrine system.

123
00:10:12,152 --> 00:10:15,231
For someone
with a disrupted endocrine system,

124
00:10:15,231 --> 00:10:16,751
it's quite dangerous.

125
00:10:18,631 --> 00:10:21,111
No other medication was found
in Pang Xinghua's home.

126
00:10:21,751 --> 00:10:24,871
Shouldn't he have gone to the hospital
immediately in this situation?

127
00:10:25,871 --> 00:10:30,111
The elevator surveillance shows

128
00:10:30,111 --> 00:10:31,631
that when Pang Xinghua returned,

129
00:10:31,631 --> 00:10:32,831
dawn was approaching.

130
00:10:33,312 --> 00:10:36,631
We can't know how he returned home.

131
00:10:37,111 --> 00:10:38,912
He never came out after returning home.

132
00:10:39,831 --> 00:10:41,512
Pang Xianglan visited him once

133
00:10:41,512 --> 00:10:43,471
a few hours after he returned.

134
00:10:43,792 --> 00:10:45,991
But she stayed for only a few minutes
before leaving.

135
00:10:48,471 --> 00:10:50,312
At 7 AM in the morning after the crime,

136
00:10:51,111 --> 00:10:52,591
you went to see Pang Xinghua, right?

137
00:10:54,111 --> 00:10:54,871
Why?

138
00:10:57,912 --> 00:10:58,792
My brother...

139
00:11:00,831 --> 00:11:02,351
I was just checking on him.

140
00:11:11,831 --> 00:11:13,176
According to communications list,

141
00:11:13,432 --> 00:11:16,831
Pang Xinghua called you 17 times
on the night of the crime.

142
00:11:16,831 --> 00:11:17,871
You didn't answer any.

143
00:11:18,792 --> 00:11:19,552
Why?

144
00:11:21,711 --> 00:11:24,111
My phone was out of battery at the time.

145
00:11:25,111 --> 00:11:29,272
At 5 AM in the next morning,
Pang Xinghua called you again.

146
00:11:30,152 --> 00:11:31,432
But you answered.

147
00:11:32,192 --> 00:11:32,951
What did you say?

148
00:11:34,432 --> 00:11:36,272
I had just charged my phone.

149
00:11:36,751 --> 00:11:39,631
I asked about why he called me

150
00:11:40,312 --> 00:11:41,792
and if he had taken his medication.

151
00:11:42,192 --> 00:11:45,231
After seeing that many missed calls,

152
00:11:45,231 --> 00:11:46,192
especially from family,

153
00:11:47,512 --> 00:11:48,991
anybody would call back immediately,

154
00:11:48,991 --> 00:11:50,552
fearing it might be urgent.

155
00:12:01,951 --> 00:12:03,392
This was captured

156
00:12:04,312 --> 00:12:06,631
when you left his home,
the night before the crime.

157
00:12:07,672 --> 00:12:09,272
You looked very emotional.

158
00:12:10,552 --> 00:12:11,471
What happened?

159
00:12:13,032 --> 00:12:13,831
Nothing.

160
00:12:14,831 --> 00:12:16,672
I just had an argument with my brother.

161
00:12:17,831 --> 00:12:18,711
About what?

162
00:12:20,192 --> 00:12:21,392
What else?

163
00:12:23,471 --> 00:12:24,272
About money.

164
00:12:25,032 --> 00:12:28,672
His gambling debts were due soon,
and he couldn't pay.

165
00:12:29,751 --> 00:12:31,392
He wanted me to get him money again.

166
00:12:32,072 --> 00:12:34,672
I told him I couldn't.

167
00:12:35,831 --> 00:12:37,032
Then he started a fight.

168
00:12:38,871 --> 00:12:42,111
So I left in anger.

169
00:12:43,591 --> 00:12:45,912
Did Pang Xinghua often ask you
to pay off his debts?

170
00:12:48,192 --> 00:12:52,351
He used my phone number
when borrowing money.

171
00:12:53,512 --> 00:12:56,951
I paid them off before too.

172
00:12:57,751 --> 00:12:58,951
Why not this time?

173
00:12:58,951 --> 00:13:00,711
I really had no way out.

174
00:13:01,351 --> 00:13:03,152
My salary is not high.

175
00:13:03,152 --> 00:13:04,631
I earn less than he spends.

176
00:13:05,591 --> 00:13:09,951
I've borrowed money
from everyone possible,

177
00:13:09,951 --> 00:13:11,792
like my friends,
colleagues, and clients.

178
00:13:12,751 --> 00:13:14,912
I honestly couldn't bring myself
to do that again.

179
00:13:20,152 --> 00:13:23,192
Do you know
about his relationship with Zhan Qiuman?

180
00:13:24,351 --> 00:13:28,871
They're from the same hometown,
so somewhat familiar.

181
00:13:29,072 --> 00:13:31,351
Did he know
about Zhan Qiuman's financial situation?

182
00:13:32,152 --> 00:13:34,591
He might have heard about it
casually in conversation before.

183
00:13:35,591 --> 00:13:36,871
Who knew he would...

184
00:13:39,272 --> 00:13:40,792
Man was a pitiful person too,

185
00:13:42,512 --> 00:13:43,432
just like me.

186
00:13:45,512 --> 00:13:48,871
Tell us about your meeting
with your brother that morning.

187
00:14:20,056 --> 00:14:20,644
(Place Your Bets)

188
00:14:26,032 --> 00:14:27,152
Are you trying to die?

189
00:14:27,432 --> 00:14:29,072
Don't you know how bad your health is?

190
00:14:29,591 --> 00:14:31,912
And you ate sweets and drank alcohol?

191
00:14:37,591 --> 00:14:38,312
What's wrong?

192
00:14:39,991 --> 00:14:41,072
Didn't get a shot again?

193
00:14:43,672 --> 00:14:44,591
Any medication at home?

194
00:14:44,912 --> 00:14:45,631
I'll get it for you.

195
00:14:47,111 --> 00:14:47,711
Xianglan.

196
00:14:49,991 --> 00:14:52,111
Xianglan, you have to help me.

197
00:14:53,351 --> 00:14:54,792
You must help me this time.

198
00:14:55,871 --> 00:14:56,951
If you don't help me,

199
00:14:57,512 --> 00:14:58,751
I'll die, Xianglan.

200
00:15:00,631 --> 00:15:01,272
Xianglan.

201
00:15:02,672 --> 00:15:04,512
Xianglan, I'm begging you.

202
00:15:05,432 --> 00:15:06,032
Xianglan.

203
00:15:07,192 --> 00:15:08,032
You have to help me.

204
00:15:09,711 --> 00:15:12,591
I genuinely thought
he was skipping his shots on purpose

205
00:15:12,591 --> 00:15:14,312
to force me into paying his debts.

206
00:15:15,032 --> 00:15:16,471
He had pulled the same trick

207
00:15:16,471 --> 00:15:17,512
a million times.

208
00:15:19,432 --> 00:15:20,351
I thought

209
00:15:21,272 --> 00:15:25,152
he'd eventually get his shot anyway.

210
00:15:26,032 --> 00:15:28,591
Did you know
he had no insulin left at home?

211
00:15:29,512 --> 00:15:31,272
That's what he told me.

212
00:15:33,591 --> 00:15:34,672
But I didn't believe him.

213
00:15:37,991 --> 00:15:42,711
Did you buy medication for him?

214
00:15:43,231 --> 00:15:44,912
Or did he buy it himself?

215
00:15:45,432 --> 00:15:46,392
Himself.

216
00:15:48,072 --> 00:15:49,991
He's a grown man.

217
00:15:49,991 --> 00:15:51,111
He should

218
00:15:51,111 --> 00:15:52,711
handle such basic things himself.

219
00:15:53,711 --> 00:15:55,351
It's been about a week

220
00:15:56,072 --> 00:16:00,392
since his death. During that time,

221
00:16:01,831 --> 00:16:03,351
you didn't contact him,

222
00:16:04,351 --> 00:16:05,512
nor visit him.

223
00:16:06,512 --> 00:16:07,512
What's the reason?

224
00:16:11,272 --> 00:16:13,672
I was furious then.

225
00:16:14,831 --> 00:16:17,512
I-I said harsh things.

226
00:16:18,072 --> 00:16:21,512
I told him I'd cut our ties

227
00:16:21,631 --> 00:16:23,351
and leave him behind to rot.

228
00:16:24,831 --> 00:16:26,272
I was truly exhausted.

229
00:16:27,912 --> 00:16:32,231
I've looked after him since childhood.

230
00:16:33,231 --> 00:16:34,792
I always supported him.

231
00:16:37,991 --> 00:16:43,192
I spent too much time
cleaning up his messes.

232
00:16:44,032 --> 00:16:44,831
I...

233
00:16:46,711 --> 00:16:47,552
I'm just...

234
00:16:50,591 --> 00:16:54,312
Did Pang Xinghua mention anything else
during the meeting?

235
00:16:56,471 --> 00:16:57,351
No.

236
00:16:59,111 --> 00:17:03,312
I scolded him and left.

237
00:17:14,952 --> 00:17:15,631
Master.

238
00:17:17,232 --> 00:17:18,351
Can we close this case?

239
00:17:19,631 --> 00:17:21,472
The evidence
against Pang Xinghua is solid.

240
00:17:22,032 --> 00:17:23,952
No doubts about his death either.

241
00:17:24,512 --> 00:17:25,911
We can proceed with formalities.

242
00:17:26,671 --> 00:17:27,272
Okay.

243
00:17:27,752 --> 00:17:28,952
How's another case?

244
00:17:31,312 --> 00:17:32,272
No movement.

245
00:17:40,191 --> 00:17:41,472
Two bottles of mineral water.

246
00:17:41,472 --> 00:17:41,752
(Order, Pick up)

247
00:17:41,752 --> 00:17:42,072
(Line up, Thanks)

248
00:17:42,072 --> 00:17:42,631
Got it.

249
00:17:52,671 --> 00:17:53,472
I've paid.

250
00:17:53,472 --> 00:17:53,992
Thanks.

251
00:18:08,391 --> 00:18:10,671
I have two tickets to a theme park.

252
00:18:11,151 --> 00:18:11,831
Are you going?

253
00:18:12,312 --> 00:18:13,111
Not interested.

254
00:18:14,512 --> 00:18:16,191
The tickets are hard to get.

255
00:18:16,431 --> 00:18:17,911
Your crush has asked you out.

256
00:18:19,591 --> 00:18:21,631
You should reciprocate.

257
00:18:21,871 --> 00:18:23,552
If you don't go, I'll ask Little Zhao.

258
00:18:27,151 --> 00:18:28,752
You always ignore me.

259
00:18:28,752 --> 00:18:30,151
What are you looking at?

260
00:18:30,431 --> 00:18:32,312
Si Yuanlong, give it back to me.

261
00:18:32,312 --> 00:18:32,871
Back off.

262
00:18:32,871 --> 00:18:34,191
I won't breathe a word.

263
00:18:34,191 --> 00:18:34,712
Give it back.

264
00:18:39,472 --> 00:18:40,631
You're mad again?

265
00:18:41,712 --> 00:18:43,111
Over something this small?

266
00:18:47,871 --> 00:18:49,072
So petty.

267
00:18:52,216 --> 00:18:54,912
(From Dan Qing, Are you free
this weekend? Let's meet up.)

268
00:18:59,552 --> 00:19:00,191
What is it?

269
00:19:04,472 --> 00:19:05,631
She is asking you out.

270
00:19:11,224 --> 00:19:15,686
(Outpatient)

271
