501
00:36:42,231 --> 00:36:43,751
But she...

502
00:36:44,151 --> 00:36:44,711
She...

503
00:36:47,072 --> 00:36:48,512
In panic, I pushed her.

504
00:36:49,311 --> 00:36:52,072
Then she...

505
00:36:54,311 --> 00:36:54,912
Xianglan.

506
00:36:55,271 --> 00:36:56,552
Xianglan, I didn't mean that.

507
00:36:56,912 --> 00:36:58,231
I really didn't mean to.

508
00:36:58,751 --> 00:36:59,791
Xianglan, please help me.

509
00:37:02,352 --> 00:37:03,231
What is Man's body?

510
00:37:08,472 --> 00:37:11,032
I called you yesterday,
but you didn't answer.

511
00:37:12,552 --> 00:37:13,472
I was helpless.

512
00:37:15,472 --> 00:37:16,671
So I drove her car

513
00:37:18,352 --> 00:37:19,552
and threw her into the river.

514
00:37:23,151 --> 00:37:24,352
Did anyone see that?

515
00:37:26,591 --> 00:37:28,072
I don't know.

516
00:37:28,631 --> 00:37:29,392
I don't know.

517
00:37:31,231 --> 00:37:33,191
When you told Man to come find you,

518
00:37:33,711 --> 00:37:34,872
did anyone else know it?

519
00:37:34,952 --> 00:37:35,872
I don't know.

520
00:37:35,872 --> 00:37:37,832
How would I know
if she told someone else?

521
00:37:42,591 --> 00:37:43,151
You...

522
00:37:45,311 --> 00:37:46,352
You didn't take your shot?

523
00:37:47,872 --> 00:37:48,631
I did.

524
00:37:50,711 --> 00:37:51,512
I took it, I guess.

525
00:37:51,671 --> 00:37:52,631
Any medication at home?

526
00:37:53,231 --> 00:37:54,072
I'll get it for you.

527
00:37:54,231 --> 00:37:56,631
I remember I put it in the car.

528
00:38:02,591 --> 00:38:03,392
There's no medicine.

529
00:38:03,392 --> 00:38:04,832
Why didn't you get more?

530
00:38:05,552 --> 00:38:05,992
Xianglan.

531
00:38:05,992 --> 00:38:07,671
Hold on. Hang in there.

532
00:38:07,832 --> 00:38:09,392
I'll go buy medicine for you right now.

533
00:38:09,671 --> 00:38:10,392
Hang in there.

534
00:38:10,392 --> 00:38:11,231
Hang in there!

535
00:38:12,552 --> 00:38:13,191
Xianglan.

536
00:38:15,352 --> 00:38:16,032
Xianglan.

537
00:38:16,271 --> 00:38:18,111
Xianglan.

538
00:39:30,151 --> 00:39:31,151
If he doesn't get a shot,

539
00:39:32,072 --> 00:39:33,432
he'll die.

540
00:39:35,111 --> 00:39:37,791
If he gets it, you'll die with him.

541
00:39:39,631 --> 00:39:41,992
If he...

542
00:39:42,432 --> 00:39:45,432
He's my little brother!

543
00:39:45,952 --> 00:39:49,392
He just sees you as a cash machine.

544
00:39:50,271 --> 00:39:53,631
Before Mom and Dad passed,
they entrusted him to me.

545
00:39:53,631 --> 00:39:57,872
They said
our family line couldn't die out.

546
00:39:58,032 --> 00:39:59,872
He is a parasite.

547
00:39:59,992 --> 00:40:01,631
It's no big deal to lose him.

548
00:40:02,591 --> 00:40:05,111
He is doomed anyway.

549
00:40:13,231 --> 00:40:17,231
I can't just stand by and watch him die.

550
00:40:18,751 --> 00:40:19,671
I can't do it.

551
00:40:20,072 --> 00:40:22,392
Every time he dumped his mess on you,

552
00:40:22,872 --> 00:40:24,631
he didn't feel sorry at all.

553
00:40:28,671 --> 00:40:31,432
Anyway, I've been taking care of him.

554
00:40:33,791 --> 00:40:37,072
Maybe I just suffer
for a few more years.

555
00:40:37,671 --> 00:40:38,671
Just a few more years.

556
00:40:38,952 --> 00:40:41,311
But how much time is left for yourself?

557
00:40:42,832 --> 00:40:46,352
Are you really willing
to be dragged down by him

558
00:40:46,392 --> 00:40:47,912
until the day you die?

559
00:40:49,472 --> 00:40:52,591
You've just been brainwashed
by your parents.

560
00:40:53,271 --> 00:40:54,671
You're also their kid.

561
00:40:55,711 --> 00:40:58,432
Why should you
have to take care of their son,

562
00:40:58,432 --> 00:40:59,311
support him,

563
00:40:59,512 --> 00:41:01,111
and give in to him in everything?

564
00:41:02,072 --> 00:41:03,952
Why were you the one
supporting the parents

565
00:41:04,032 --> 00:41:05,512
and working hard to earn money?

566
00:41:05,512 --> 00:41:08,992
Yet they had been thinking of him
until their death.

567
00:41:12,591 --> 00:41:13,992
He's my brother.

568
00:41:13,992 --> 00:41:16,432
He's a grown man.
How could he live off of you

569
00:41:16,671 --> 00:41:18,591
like a parasite?

570
00:41:18,591 --> 00:41:20,631
- He will chew you up.
- He's my brother.

571
00:41:20,912 --> 00:41:21,992
Don't you hate him?

572
00:41:22,271 --> 00:41:23,952
- He's my brother!
- Have you never thought

573
00:41:24,791 --> 00:41:26,512
about getting rid of him?

574
00:41:27,472 --> 00:41:28,751
He is my...

575
00:41:30,191 --> 00:41:31,912
He's my brother.

576
00:41:33,671 --> 00:41:34,631
Be honest.

577
00:41:35,952 --> 00:41:39,191
Have you never thought
about killing him?

578
00:41:43,552 --> 00:41:44,392
He is...

579
00:41:46,472 --> 00:41:48,392
He's my brother.

580
00:42:29,832 --> 00:42:30,872
（I know

581
00:42:31,832 --> 00:42:36,191
you want to go far away from here.）

582
00:42:43,129 --> 00:42:46,622
♪Replacing the weight of tears
with that of sweat♪

583
00:42:50,416 --> 00:42:55,737
♪Covering the gunshot's sound
with wounds♪

584
00:42:57,810 --> 00:43:02,664
♪No one is born unyielding and strong♪

585
00:43:03,470 --> 00:43:06,617
♪But because someone
always rushes ahead♪

586
00:43:06,617 --> 00:43:09,721
♪To shield us from the storm♪

587
00:43:12,377 --> 00:43:17,511
♪When every extraordinary act
becomes routine♪

588
00:43:19,481 --> 00:43:25,113
♪Just to polish the badge
upon their shoulder♪

589
00:43:26,873 --> 00:43:30,457
♪Like light surging unseen
through the night♪

590
00:43:31,609 --> 00:43:39,049
♪Converging into your form♪

591
00:43:39,481 --> 00:43:42,159
♪Looking up♪

592
00:43:42,159 --> 00:43:45,698
♪Such dazzling glory♪

593
00:43:46,681 --> 00:43:49,241
♪Like hope♪

594
00:43:49,241 --> 00:43:53,174
♪Reaching out its arms♪

595
00:43:54,041 --> 00:43:56,693
♪Cloaked in light♪

596
00:43:56,693 --> 00:44:01,177
♪Alone, they charge ahead♪

597
00:44:01,177 --> 00:44:03,993
♪Traversing♪

598
00:44:03,993 --> 00:44:10,504
♪The battlefield of fate♪
